			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">While driving to work today I was contemplating all the similar issues, complaints, whining or whatever you want to call it that I see for almost every class on their respective boards.  Most of this revolves around the "inabilty" to do something another class can or they feel is needed or would "balance" their class.  I myself have these thoughts occasionally as I am sure many of us have.
<br />
 
<br />
Rather then dwell on what I can't do I instead asked myself how can SoE possibly make all classes happy.  While I don't suggest I have the answer I do have an idea.  It centers around AA's and only brings change at the high end of a PC's life but I thought it may be interesting to discuss so here it is:
<br />
 
<br />
AA:       Mastery of the arcane
<br />
Cost:    20 points
<br />
Required level:  70
<br />
Effect:  Increases spell slots by one for all classes, (up to 10 for casters and 1 for non caster melee)
<br />
Description:  Through intense study of all forms of the arcane you have developed the ability to memorize on additional spell of any arcane spell type up to and including level 60 spells. (Complete heal excluded)  The one draw back of this is once you have scribed this spell in your spell book it is non-removable and can never be attempted again.
<br />
 
<br />
I can only think of what fun this could be for the melee with the ability to cast a heal over time, or a rogue to mezz.  The possibilities are endless and would allow for the tuning of the play style you prefer,  IE, a Monk that likes to solo may pick a slow or a heal as an option while a grouping monk may chose pacify for pulling.
<br />
 
<br />
There are a few hurdles, melee spell books and mana pool.  Perhaps for melee it is scribed as a reusable disc that works off of endurance rather then mana.
<br />
 
<br />
Either way I like the flexibility it gives the high end gamer and the utility all players could enjoy.
<br />
 
<br />
Thoughts?
<br />
Ninka
<br />
69th Magus
<br />
Sol Ro</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
