			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have thought for a long time that this could be a good idea, now all players of the same class are essentially the same - such as all level 70 mages give the approximately the same benefit to a group, this would be a chance for a player to further individualize himself, a good deal of thought would need to be given to the actual abilities or spells given to players to maintain balance (and we all know how concerned sony is about maintaining balance), 
<br />

<br />
I think allowing casters to choose a spell casting specialty was supposed to accomplish this same idea, but it really never delivered the distinction between players of different specialties that I had hoped for, you never see a group looking for a druid specialized in alteration - either they want a druid or they don't,
<br />

<br />
we used to talk about the "holy trinity" of warrior-cleric-chanter as basis of a top notch group, now that has evolved to be tank-healer-CC-puller-slower as the basis of a top group, 5 of the 6 slots for the group is filled with roles we cannot perform, adding one extra ability might help us mages be able to find groups a little easier, 
<br />

<br />
yes, allowing this would further blur the distinction between the classes - so what!, druids can heal, nuke, buff, snare, root, port, have pets, that sounds like they have a pretty blurry class distinction, beastlords can slow, buff, paragon, cast hp/mana regen, keep their pets alive longer than a mage can, even heal a little, again-pretty blurry class distinction, how could this make it any worse?
<br />

<br />
I am in favor of an AA ability that would allow a level 70 player to gain one single ability or spell of another class, that ability or spell gained would be a level 55-60 version of that spell or ability, proabaly would work best if it was done as an AA ability, using no mana, and having some type of recast delay, recast delay would vary according to the actual ability chosen
<br />

<br />
abilities would have to be made so all were equally desirable, would not want everyone to automatically choose slow, would need to make ac/hp buff ability as attractive as slow or nuke ability, these abilites would still be secondary to the main function of each class, a mage that can cast a 20 second mez is not going to replace a chanter and a warrior that can cast a 500 point heal is not going to replace a cleric-but would be nice to have that ability whent he scat hits the fan</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
