			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Given the chance to take one spell from any class, nobody would take a mage spell.  Not when you could have FD, heals, slow, or snare instead.
<br />

<br />
This idea would be cripling to classes who hold most of their balance in a single spell such as CH or Turgur's.
<br />

<br />
If you are going to exclude CH and 96% rez as game-breaking then you need to put Turgurs on that list too.  Making these unavailable will also preserve the demand for the shaman and clerics though.  
<br />

<br />
If you're going to give clerics and shaman special consideration then you need to protect other classes defining abilities too like FD, CoH, mage pets, corpse summoning, it goes on and on.  
<br />

<br />
As you remove spells, another crops up in it's place as being over-powered in comparison to the rest available, and would therefore impact the classes being robbed unfairly.
<br />

<br />
You get left with abilities like root, snare, gate, invis, DA...<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=546815" target=_blank>Sarye Starfyre</a> 
<br />
Blood Cult
<br />
Xev</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
